gmd:title.gco:CharacterString: Traffic Counts on Roadways (from INDOT Statewide Travel Demand MODEL version 4, ISTDM4): Indiana, 2004

gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString: TRAFFIC_COUNTS_INDOTMODEL_IN is a line shapefile that shows traffic counts (factored to year 2000) for the roadways in the Indiana Statewide Travel Demand Model, version4, (ISTDM4). Annual average daily traffic (AADT) counts are in the units of average vehicles/day. This file is a subset of the Indiana Statewide Travel Demand Model, version4, (ISTDM4).

gmd:purpose.gco:CharacterString: Planning and Development of Interstate 69 from Evansville to Indianapolis. The model from which this shapefile was created was intended to duplicate general traffic patterns, therefore detailed network at interchanges and ramps are not represented.

gmd:useLimitation.gco:CharacterString: Please acknowledge the Indiana Department of Transportation
None. Data is expected to have some minimal error. User is responsible to determine appropriate use and display of the data.

gmd:title.gco:CharacterString: Indiana Statewide Travel Demand Model, version 4 (ISTDM4)

gmd:environmentDescription.gco:CharacterString: ESRI ArcView version 3.2 shapefile format, approximately 2.6 Mb

gmd:measureDescription.gco:CharacterString: Not all roadways (22%) have traffic count data and are indicated by an AADT attribute of -999999. Use and revision has revealed no Interstate, US, or State Highway which is not represented in this file. County and local roadways are not complete and limited to only those included in the model which was the base for this file. The model from which this shapefile was created was intended to duplicate general traffic patterns, therefore detailed network at interchanges and ramps are not represented.

The Attributes have undergone a history of updates and revisions. They are believed to be highly accurate, however; no field survey has been done to provide a quantitative measure. Traffic counts were added from a variety of the best sources available.
Unknown, however use with high accuracy imagery (1-m DOQQs) has shown roadway positions to be highly accurate.

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: The base_2000 file from the Indiana Statewide Travel Demand Model, version 4, (ISTDM4) was converted in TransCAD to an ESRI ArcView Shapefile. Roadways were selected to those in Indiana by querying a boolean field for Indiana. All roadways in the model were included in the subset, however centroid connectors were removed. Numerous attribute fields were removed to result in the basic roadway information.

This metadata file was pre-parsed and parsed using CNS (Chew and Spit, v. 2.6.1) and MP (Metadata Parser, v. 2.7.1) software written by Peter N. Schweitzer (U.S. Geological Survey). The errors generated by MP were all addressed and corrected.
Base file for subsets of transportation features.

gmd:title.gco:CharacterString: Indiana Statewide Travel Demand Model, version 4 (ISTDM4)

gmd:otherCitationDetails.gco:CharacterString: The model has evolved through a series of revisions and modifications since 1996. The first road lines were from TIGER 1980 Line files which were used to create the CASPER snow plow routing system. The roads were updated and attributed in 1996 using the INDOT 1996 Road Inventory Database. This 1996 version was used in the 1997 Statewide Travel Demand Model. Local roads were added to the model in 1998 as part of the Statewide Interstate Interchange Study, and all roads were updated using the INDOT 1998 Road Inventory Database. Nearby roadways in Illinois, Kentucky, Ohio, and Michigan were added in 1999. More local roads in Southwestern Indiana were added in 1999 - 2000. Updates and revisions occur as the model is used. Traffic counts were obtained from the 1998 Indot Road Inventory Database. Some were updated by manual counts in 2000. The model was again updated in 2003-2004, creating version 4 of the Statewide Travel Demand Model (ISTDM4). Additional county and local roads were added to the model network. State jurisdictional roadways were updated using the INDOT 2000 Road Inventory Database. Traffic count data was updated from the INDOT 2000 Road Inventory Database, as well as other best available sources (INDOT counts, MPO/RPO counts, and bridge inventory counts). For more detailed information on the development and use of the model, contact INDOT through: (1) Steve Smith, Systems Planning Coordinator, 317-232-5646 (2) Kirk Mangold, Program Developement, 317-233-1061 (3) the "Travel Model User's Guide" (Task 3.3.3.1 Technical Report) " printed March 2001 as part of the I-69 Evansville to Indianapolis Study, Tier 1 Environmental Impact Statement,Vol 1. (4) the "Travel Model User's Guide" for the Indiana Statewide Travel Demand Model, version 4 (ISTDM4)

IGS/BLA does not support secondary distribution. If this data set was received from anyone besides the IGS/BLA, this metadata file and the data set it describes may lack integrity.
